Package: bioplotr
Title: Pretty, simple, optionally interactive plots for bioinformatics analysis 
  pipelines
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("David", "Watson", email = "d.watson@qmul.ac.uk", 
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package provides functions to build many common (and some not 
  so common) figures for omic data analysis. Most plots employ a "Grammar of 
  Graphics" framework, with optional plotly and shiny add-ons for interactive
  functionality and HTML output. 
Depends: R (>= 3.3.2)
Imports: 
  dplyr,
  ggplot2,
  tidyr,
  purrr,
  plotly,
  NMF,
  edgeR,
  matrixStats,
  scales,
  ModelMetrics,
  PRROC,
  wordspace
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
